          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Career and Technical Education Opportunity Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends title IV (Student Assistance) of the Higher Education Act of 1965 to expand the programs eligible to participate in federal student aid.</p> <p>Specifically, it makes eligible for Direct Loan program and Federal Perkins Loan program participation an educational program that provides at least 250 hours of instruction over a minimum of 5 weeks that leads to an industry-recognized credential.</p> <p>An industry-recognized credential: (1) is high quality, as demonstrated by the institution offering the program; (2) meets local or regional workforce needs; and (3) is endorsed by a national industry trade association. </p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
